This paper discusses the use of word embeddings in natural language processing tasks, which is a common topic in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses partial least squares regression, which is a statistical technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on modeling language semantics could also place it in the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper's use of datasets and evaluation metrics suggests a potential fit for the subfield of software engineering (cs.SD).
